 That crash prompted the United States and its NATO allies to agree to suspend all A-10 flights over West Germany until Jan. 2.
 On the same day as the crash in Remscheid, an A-10 crashed near the heart of the Tohono O'Odham Indian Reservation, about 80 miles west of Tuscon, but the pilot ejected safely.
